## UI/UX Features

Below is a detailed breakdown of each UI/UX component, how it is implemented, and examples of relevant code snippets.

### 1. Global Box-Sizing Reset

**Purpose:** Ensure predictable sizing by including padding and borders within set widths/heights.

```css
/* Place at the very top of your stylesheet */
*, *::before, *::after {
  box-sizing: border-box;
}
```

- Applies the `border-box` model to all elements and their pseudo-elements.
- Prevents unwanted horizontal overflow when combining `width: 100%` with padding.

---

### 2. Theming with CSS Variables

**Purpose:** Centralize color schemes and enable light/dark mode toggling.

```css
:root {
  --light-bg: #f5f6fa;
  --dark-bg:  #23272f;
  --light-primary: #0057b8;
  --dark-primary:  #4ea1ff;
  /* ...other variables... */
}

body {
  background: var(--light-bg);
  color:      var(--light-text);
  transition: background 0.3s, color 0.3s;
}

body.dark-mode {
  background: var(--dark-bg);
  color:      var(--dark-text);
}
```

- Variables are declared in `:root` for global scope.
- The `.dark-mode` class on `<body>` swaps to dark variables.
- Smooth transitions enhance UX during mode switch.

---

### 3. Sticky, Responsive Header

**Purpose:** Keep primary navigation visible at all times; adapt layout between mobile/desktop.

```css
.header {
  position: sticky;
  top: 0;
  padding: 0 16px;
  height: 56px;
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  align-items: center;
  background: var(--light-header);
  z-index: 1000;
}

@media (min-width: 700px) {
  .header { height: 72px; padding: 0 40px; }
}
```

- `position: sticky; top: 0;` ensures the header remains pinned.
- Flexbox distributes logo and controls.
- Media query adjusts sizing for desktop.

---

### 4. Navigation System

#### Desktop Navigation

- **HTML structure:** `<nav> → <ul> → <li.nav-item> → <a.nav-link>` or `<button.nav-link>` for submenus.
- **Hover and focus:**
  ```css
  .nav-link:hover {
    background: var(--light-nav-hover);
  }
  ```
- **Dropdowns:**
  ```css
  .nav-item:hover .dropdown {
    display: flex;
  }
  ```

#### Mobile Navigation

- Controlled via a hamburger button that toggles `.active` on `.mobile-menu` and `.overlay`.
- Slide-in panel:
  ```css
  .mobile-menu {
    transform: translateX(100%);
    transition: transform 0.3s;
  }
  .mobile-menu.active {
    transform: translateX(0);
  }
  ```
- Submenus expand on button click (for width < 700px) by toggling `.open` on `.nav-item`.

---

### 5. Dropdown Behavior and Focus Management

**Challenge:** Prevent dropdowns from persisting after clicking or focusing inside.

**Solution:** Use hover-only for display, avoid `:focus-within`:

```css
.nav-item:hover .dropdown,
.nav-item .nav-link[aria-haspopup]:focus + .dropdown {
  display: flex;
}
```

Optionally blur after submenu clicks:
```js
document.querySelectorAll('.dropdown a').forEach(link => {
  link.addEventListener('click', () => {
    const btn = link.closest('.nav-item')
                   .querySelector('.nav-link[aria-haspopup]');
    if (btn) btn.blur();
  });
});
```

---

### 6. Hero Section

- Full‐width background with centered content:
  ```css
  .hero {
    height: 260px;
    background: url('...') center/cover no-repeat;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
  }
  .hero::after {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: rgba(0,87,184,0.45);
  }
  ```

- Media query increases height to `420px` on desktop.

---

### 7. Content Sections

- Alternating background colors using `:nth-child`:
  ```css
  .section:nth-child(even) { background: var(--light-bg-alt); }
  .section:nth-child(odd)  { background: var(--light-bg); }
  ```

- Responsive padding and max-width adjustments for readability.

---

### 8. Footer

- Simple centered content.
- Transitions on background and text color for dark mode.

---

### 9. Accessibility

- **Keyboard navigation:**
  - `:focus-visible` can be added to highlight links when tabbing.
  - ESC key listener to close mobile panel:
    ```js
